Title: Good-Enough Software
Q1: I think there's lots of evidence organizations/developes are
    comfortable shipping incompete software. I would prefer simpler software
    with fewer defects, but that doesn't seem to be the current trend.
Q2: n/a
Q3: Yes, most popular software suffers from feature bloat. Examples
    include MS office suite, which are bloated with features and, for likely good reasons,
    contain a multitude of unrelated features in their products. More recently,
    Instagram has added more complex features which detract from the user
    experience but likely are required in order for the app to compete with
    it's competators